IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE MISSION OF NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES, INC., IS TO PROVIDE EXCELLENT, AFFORDABLE HEALTH CARE IN THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE.
IRS990.Description: THE ORGANIZATION'S MEDICAL SERVICES INCLUDE PRIMARY CARE, PREVENTIVE CARE, PEDIATRICS, WOMEN'S HEALTH, AND HEALTH EDUCATION. SEE SCHEDULE O FOR MORE DETAIL.

Activity2.Description: THE ORGANIZATION'S DENTAL CLINICS OFFER A FULL COMPLEMENT OF PREVENTATIVE AND RESTORATIVE CARE FOR YOUR TEETH. PREVENTATIVE SERVICES INCLUDE CLEANINGS, SEALANTS, CHECK-UPS AND X-RAYS, FILLINGS, EXTRACTIONS, ORAL CANCER SCREENING, AND HEALTHY GUM CARE. RESTORATIVE SERVICES INCLUDE ROOT CANALS, CROWNS AND BRIDGES, AND FULL AND PARTIAL DENTURES. THERE ARE THREE CONVENIENT LOCATIONS IN SAVANNAH, ST JOSEPH, AND MOUND CITY.

Activity3.Description: THE ORGANIZATION INTEGRATES BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES INTO DISEASE MANAGEMENT, PRIMARY, AND PREVENTATIVE CARE. BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES INCLUDE ASSESSMENT AND PRIVATE CONSULTATION, GROUP THERAPY, PHARMACOLOGICAL SUPPORTS, FAMILY COUNSELING, AND REFERRALS.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS A COMMUNITY VOLUNTEER BOARD. ORGANIZATION'S MISSION FORM 990, PART III, LINE 1 THE MISSION OF NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES, INC., IS TO PROVIDE EXCELLENT, AFFORDABLE HEALTH CARE IN THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE. OUR MISSION IS SUPPORTED THROUGH THE ORGANIZATION'S VALUES WHICH ARE QUALITY, EQUALITY, INTEGRITY, RESPECT, AND COMPASSION. PROVIDING ACCESS TO PATIENT CENTERED, QUALITY HEALTH CARE FOR THOSE THAT ARE UNINSURED, UNDERINSURED, OR UTILIZING GOVERNMENT ASSISTANCE IS TOP PRIORITY. NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES TREATS EACH PATIENT EQUALLY WITH INTEGRITY, RESPECT AND COMPASSION, REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY. PROVIDING ACCESS TO QUALITY MEDICAL, DENTAL, BEHAVIORAL HEALTH, PHARMACEUTICAL, AND HEALTH EDUCATION IS HOW NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES ACHIEVES THIS MISSION. COMMUNITY OUTREACH AND EDUCATION ARE ALSO A MEANS TO ACCOMPLISH THE MISSION. OUR COMMUNITY-LED BOARD OF DIRECTORS REPRESENTS THE AREAS WE SERVE AND GUIDES THE ORGANIZATION TO PROVIDING THE BEST CARE POSSIBLE BASED ON THE NEEDS OF THE COMMUNITIES. AS A COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER, NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES IS PROUD TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE COMMUNITIES WE SERVE. MEDICAL SERVICES FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4A PRIMARY CARE INCLUDES PRENATAL CARE, CHILDREN'S HEALTHCARE, ADULT HEALTHCARE, AND PHYSICAL EXAMS. PREVENTATIVE CARE SERVICES INCLUDE VACCINATIONS, HEALTH SCREENINGS, NUTRITIONAL COUNSELING, AND EDUCATION. THE ORGANIZATION PROVIDES PEDIATRIC SERVICES FOR CHILDREN THROUGH THE AGE OF 18. PEDIATRIC SERVICES PROVIDED ARE WELL-CHILD HEALTH MAINTENANCE EXAMS, TREATMENT OF ACUTE AND CHRONIC PROBLEMS, REFERRAL WHEN NEEDED TO SPECIALISTS, AND HEALTH SCREENING ASSESSMENTS AND LAB TESTS FOR REFUGEE CHILDREN WHO ARE NEW ARRIVALS TO THE UNITED STATES. THE ORGANIZATION'S WOMEN'S HEALTH SERVICES INCLUDE: COMPREHENSIVE GYNECOLOGICAL EXAMS; BREAST, CERVICAL, AND COLON CANCER SCREENINGS; MENOPAUSAL MANAGEMENT; AND CONTRACEPTIVE CHOICES. OTHER SERVICES FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4D THE ORGANIZATION ALSO PROVIDES CLINICAL SERVICES AND A PHARMACY FOR PATIENTS. FAMILY RELATIONSHIP FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2 BOARD MEMBERS FIONA HUMMER AND RODNEY HUMMER ARE BROTHER-IN-LAW AND SISTER-IN-LAW.

GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 IS INITIALLY REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT. AFTER THIS REVIEW, THE FINANCE COMMITTEE THEN REVIEWS AT THEIR MEETING BEFORE PRESENTING TO THE FULL BOARD AT THEIR MONTHLY MEETING.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION REGULARLY MONITORS COMPLIANCE WITH THEIR CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY BY REQUESTING MANAGERS AND STAFF TO REPORT ANY CHANGES IN THEIR CONFLICT OF INTEREST. ANY CONFLICTS ARE SENT TO THE CORPORATE COMPLIANCE COMMITTEE. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS IDENTIFIED WITH A BOARD MEMBER, THEY ABSTAIN FROM VOTING ON ANY MATTERS RELATED TO THE CONFLICT.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINES 15A & 15B
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CEO TASKED THE DIRECTOR OF HUMAN RESOURCES TO CONDUCT A WAGE/SALARY SURVEY FOR THE PURPOSE OF UPDATING THE ORGANIZATION'S SALARY/WAGE SCALE. KEY CONCERNS WERE INTERNAL EQUITY AND EXTERNAL COMPETITION. THE SURVEY WAS CONDUCTED OVER A THREE-MONTH PERIOD USING DATA FROM THE MEDICAL GROUP MANAGEMENT ASSOCIATION (MGMA), COMPDATA HEALTHCARE SURVEY, NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS COMPENSATION SURVEY, MISSOURI PRIMARY CARE ASSOCIATION COMPENSATION SURVEY (USING LIKE DEMOGRAPHICS), AND CURRENT ORGANIZATION SALARY/WAGE DATA. THE CEO AND ALL SENIOR LEADERSHIP SALARIES WERE PART OF THIS SURVEY. DATA WAS DOCUMENTED ON AN EXCEL SPREADSHEET WITH PROPOSED RECOMMENDATIONS OF THE SENIOR LEADERSHIP. THE SALARY/WAGE SCALE WAS THEN APPROVED BY THE BOARD.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE ALL AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST FOR VIEWING AT THE ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICES OF NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES.

THE SIGNIFICANT INCREASE IN ASSETS IS DUE TO THE ORGANIZATION IN PROCESS OF REMODELING SEVERAL FACILITIES. THE PROJECT IS BEING FUNDED WITH GRANT MONIES FROM THE U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES.
THE CIO AND OWNER OF TRIGGERFISH TECHNOLOGIES, LLC, IS THE STEPSON OF THE CMO OF NORTHWEST HEALTH SERVICES, INC.
